line terminations have been dropped. They must be accepted and processed for -e ; they should be accepted for -E, but unless the terminal is configured specifically they'll have to be ignored (by default terminal line discipline is LINE which means we receive data line by line, so the line termination is not processed. We'd have to swich to character line discipline to have to process it, which could matter only if we hooked stdin to a remote process with specific line termination... So for now -E linetermination is accepted but ignored.  but for -e it must be processed. 

